<paragraph id="7001F0149C58FFF3FF44FF47EFE9FF57" blockId="7.[151,1436,152,410]" pageId="7" pageNumber="440">
<taxonomicName id="B7BE8B979C58FFF3FF44FF47EA00FF19" authorityName="Horton &amp; Thurston" authorityYear="2009" box="[198,381,152,177]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sindhusagar">
<emphasis id="42CA2C069C58FFF3FF44FF47EA00FF19" box="[198,381,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="440">H. sindhusagar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from the other species with an unconstricted uropod 2 inner ramus (
<taxonomicName id="B7BE8B979C58FFF3FAFDFF47EBABFF70" baseAuthorityName="Birstein &amp; Vinogradov" baseAuthorityYear="1955" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas">
<emphasis id="42CA2C069C58FFF3FAFDFF47EBABFF70" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="440">H. gigas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B7BE8B979C58FFF3FF66FF60EA36FF70" authorityName="Dahl" authorityYear="1959" box="[228,331,191,216]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis id="42CA2C069C58FFF3FF66FF60EA36FF70" box="[228,331,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="440">H. dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by the absence of a multi-toothed dactyl on gnathopod 1 (as in 
<taxonomicName id="B7BE8B979C58FFF3FBBDFF60EFDFFF70" baseAuthorityName="Birstein &amp; Vinogradov" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[1087,1186,191,216]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas">
<emphasis id="42CA2C069C58FFF3FBBDFF60EFDFFF70" box="[1087,1186,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="440">H. gigas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the short, broad propodus of gnathopod 1 (c.f. elongate and strongly tapering gnathopod 
<quantity id="B7465DF19C58FFF3FC6AFF3AEF68FF57" box="[1000,1045,229,255]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="7" pageNumber="440" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="B7BE8B979C58FFF3FB9EFF3AEFFFFF56" authorityName="Dahl" authorityYear="1959" box="[1052,1154,229,254]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hirondelleidae" genus="Hirondellea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis id="42CA2C069C58FFF3FB9EFF3AEFFFFF56" box="[1052,1154,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="440">H. dubia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7001F0149C58FFF3FF44FED3EA54FEE4" blockId="7.[151,1436,152,410]" pageId="7" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis id="42CA2C069C58FFF3FF44FED3EA20FE8D" box="[198,349,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="440">Distribution.</emphasis>
Off the coast of 
<collectingCountry id="08A9B0849C58FFF3FDA6FED3E9FAFE8E" box="[548,647,268,294]" name="Pakistan" pageId="7" pageNumber="440">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
in the northern Arabian Sea, Indian Ocean at depths between 1182 and 
<quantity id="B7465DF19C58FFF3FF4AFEEDEA59FEE4" box="[200,292,306,332]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.864" pageId="7" pageNumber="440" unit="m" value="1864.0">1864 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7001F0149C58FFF3FF44FE86E82DFE32" blockId="7.[151,1436,152,410]" pageId="7" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis id="42CA2C069C58FFF3FF44FE86EA37FEDA" box="[198,330,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="440">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named after the collecting locality of the Arabian Sea, which was known as the Sindhu Sagar to Indians in the Vedic period of their history.
</paragraph>
